# No Hidden Folders on ChoreBoy

ChoreBoy's locked-down environment does not reliably support hidden (dot-prefixed) directories. See `docs/DISCOVERY.md` section 4A for full details.

## Constraint

Never use dot-prefixed directory names for project metadata, app state, logs, caches, or any user-facing storage paths.

## Reason

- The ChoreBoy file manager does not show hidden folders by default, making project metadata invisible to users.
- Permission and ACL behavior for dot-prefixed directories may differ under ChoreBoy's security policies.
- Directory creation can silently fail or be denied for hidden paths.

## What to use instead

Use visible (non-dot-prefixed) directory names:

- `cbcs/` not `.cbcs/` for per-project metadata.
- `choreboy_code_studio_state/` not `.choreboy_code_studio/` for global app state.
- Same principle for any new directories: logs, caches, run state, etc.

## Scope

Applies to both per-project metadata directories and global app state directories. This includes any new storage paths introduced in future work.

## Current migration status

Migration complete: `app/core/constants.py` defines `PROJECT_META_DIRNAME = "cbcs"` and `GLOBAL_STATE_DIRNAME = "choreboy_code_studio_state"`. Agents must not introduce new dot-prefixed paths.
